Nightshift and Rat Trap continued to make their way through the dark fores=
t, the sounds of animals and birds all around them, some of them chirping a=
nd yowling at their intrusion into the domain. 

While there is no real GPS=
 system here so to speak, they are still able to navigate utilizing their i=
nternal compasses and having a general knowledge of the direction that they=
 need to go. 

Mile after mile the forest seemed almost unchanging, one tre=
e and one bush looking like any other tree and bush. Sometimes it seemed li=
ke they had came past the same river bank several times, and yet they conti=
nued on. 

The forest was, beginning to clear, the older trees finally givi=
ng way to smaller younger trees. Eventually they reached the edge of a larg=
e riverbank. The river flowed by swiftly with all sorts of fish and reptili=
an life in abundance. The sun streamed down into the opening in the trees, =
the skies above seemed open and clear, not a cloud in the skies. But most i=
mportantly there was no sign of any sweeps as well. Either they were hiding=
 well, or they were not there. 

Across the river a large was a large clear=
ing, one that opened out for nearly several hundred meters. In the middle o=
f it a battle raging! A triceratops was bellowing into the air at what look=
ed to be a small T-Rex. Small when compared to some of the larger of its sp=
ecies, but still larger than the triceratops and FAR larger than Nightshift=
 and Rat Trap as they stood off in the trees. 

So far neither of them had =
been noticed.
